24 things i learnt this year🤍

1. spend as much time as you can with the people you love, you haven’t seen tomorrow 
2. slow down, you’re doing enough - a younger version of you never even thought you’ll be where you are now
3. travel, see the world and if you can’t SAVE so you can!
4. you are ALLOWED to outgrow people, places and sometimes even YOURSELF 
5. laugh till your stomach hurts
6. take time building hobbies
7. Money is important but it’s nothing without mental peace
8. appreciate the small and big blessings in your life
9. GRATITUDE will get you places you never even thought you could be
10. be PRESENT - time lost can never be found again
11. burnout happens when you push rest to the back burner - PRIORITISE REST
12. take care of your health
13. mental health is as important as your physical health
14. check in on the people you love
15. set boundaries for scrolling on Instagram- on somedays it just makes you feel everything you don’t need to feel
16. take yourself on self pampering dates
17. set a budget - financial discipline will help you navigate your 20s
18. materialism is short-lived; experiences aren’t 
19. do more things you loved doing as a kid for ex: painting; it can help you connect with your inner child
20. be gentle on yourself, you are a WIP✨
21. Say “i love you” to people you love as often as you can
22. if something/someone isn’t serving you it’s okay to move on
23. you don’t have to enjoy the same things you friends do; you’re allowed to be different 
24. lastly be as boring, as quiet you want to be; not everyone needs to know every thought you have.

⭐️a guide to wardrobe basics⭐️

As a girl in my 20s, one thing l’ve learnt is the importance of high quality basic pieces. 20s girlies we need to be put together and spend less time thinking what to buy and making more important life decisions. SAVE this for when you may need it 🍓❤️‍🔥
